-- PowerSecure International names CFO
-- 
-- Tue Dec 11, 2007 6:53am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/11/powersecure-management-idUSWNAS422820071211

 

 Dec 11 (Reuters) - PowerSecure International Inc POWR.O
said it named Chris Hutter chief financial officer, replacing
Gary Zuiderveen, who will take up the new position of vice
president of financial reporting. 

  Hutter, 41, was most recently national vice president,
finance, treasurer, investor relations, and assistant secretary
of ADVO Inc, which was acquired by Valassis Communications Inc
( VCI.N ) in March, the company said in a statement.  Zuiderveen will continue as the company's controller and
principal accounting officer, PowerSecure added.
 (Reporting by Shamik Paul in Bangalore; Editing by Deepak
Kannan)


